3.1 clamdscan-progress
======================

Synopsis:

     clamdscan-progress [OPTION]... [PATH]...

   Important options:

‘--resume FILE’
     Resume a previous run from an existing state file.

‘--dry-run’
     Build the scan list and record progress without calling
     ‘clamdscan’.

‘--no-tracker’
     Disable Tracker pause/resume integration for the current run.

‘--system’
     Use the configured system target list instead of default targets.

‘-h, --help’
     Display built-in usage help.

   Examples:

     sudo clamdscan-progress
     sudo clamdscan-progress --system
     clamdscan-progress ~/Descargas
     sudo clamdscan-progress --resume /var/lib/clamdscan-tools/state/scan_TIMESTAMP.state


