4 Configuration
***************

The package installs the following configuration files:

‘/etc/clamdscan-tools/clamdscan-tools.conf’
     Main configuration file with default targets, runtime directories
     and optional integrations.

‘/etc/clamdscan-tools/excludes.conf’
     Directory-name exclusions such as ‘.git’, ‘node_modules’ or cache
     folders.

‘/etc/clamdscan-tools/prune-paths.conf’
     Absolute paths to skip entirely, for example ‘/proc’ or ‘/sys’.


File: clamdscan-tools.info,  Node: Runtime Files,  Prev: Configuration,  Up: Top

5 Runtime Files
***************

During execution, clamdscan-tools stores data in standard locations:

‘/var/log/clamdscan-tools/’
     Scan logs shown by ‘clamdscan-watch’.

‘/var/lib/clamdscan-tools/state/’
     State files used for resume, generated file lists and auxiliary
     logs.

‘/var/lib/clamdscan-tools/infected/’
     Destination directory for quarantined files when the scan runs with
     sufficient privileges.

   For command-specific usage, see ‘info clamdscan-tools’, ‘man
clamdscan-progress’ and ‘man clamdscan-watch’.



